result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Austin Daniel Alderman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime, Penalty-Theft if Value <=$2500, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR:  V. Kasten, Clerk: Fox, ADA:  Michael E. Nieskes, DF ATTY:  Jens Hubert Loberg, DF:  Austin Daniel Alderman appeared. Includes ARGN on 14CF250 and 14CF251; status on 14CM217. There is an agreement - Defendant to plead to and enter into an agreement for count 1 in 14CF251. Def to plead to counts 2 & 3 in 14CF251 and 14CM217.  Court reviews consequences of being convicted of a felony. Court reviews constitutional rights with def. 
Court finds def freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights. Court reads charge and possible penalties for counts 1, 2 and 3 in 14CF251 and 14CM217. Defendant pleads guilty to counts 1, 2 and 3 in 14CF251 and 14CM217. Court uses complaints/reports as factual basis, accepts plea and adjudicates def guilty of counts 2 & 3 in 14CF251 and 14CM217. Court STAYS the adjudication for count 1 in 14CF251, pending full performance of DJOC. 
RE: 14CF250 is dismissed. 
Sentence RE: 14CF251 (Cts 2 & 3) and 14CM217 -  S/W 2 years probation with conditions and concurrent: 
- Defendant shall obtain high school diploma, GED or equilivant.
- Defendant to maintain full time school or employment or a combination of both.
- Court costs 14CF251. Ct 1 = $268.00; Ct 2 = $243.00; Ct 3 = $243.00. Payable through probation.
- Court costs 14CM217 for $243.00. Apply bond on file. Payable through probation 
- Restitution to be determined within 30 days - Joint and several.
- Perform 100 hours of community service
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- Send letter of apology to victims. Submit to probation within 30 days. 
- Participate with restorative justice, if requested. 
- Not to use or posess firearm during this agreement.
- No contact with M. Kjeseth or his property.
- No contact with J. Waldroff or his property. Upon approval of probation and request of victim, the no contact to be lifted. 

Court reviews DJOC. This is a 3 year agreement. Same conditions as probation. Monitored through the District Attorney's office. 
Court approves, orders and signs agreement. Bond continues in 14CF251.
Defendant is eligible for expungement upon successful completion of probation under 973.015. Defendant to initiate. 
Defendant is advised of right to appeal. Defendant to sign up for probation today (8/22/14).

RE: 14CF250 and 14CF251 - Court informs def of charges, possible penalties and rights. Def understands.  Waives reading.  Not Guilty pleas on both cases and all counts.  Atty Loberg files preliminary hearing waivers with the Court. Court advises of rights and possible penalties regarding a preliminary hearing.  Court finds DF has freely, voluntarily, and knowingly waived the right to a preliminary hearing, finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the DF probably committed that felony and binds over for trial. Court sets bond.  Arraignment scheduled for August 22, 2014 at 10:00 am.

*Includes 14CF250 and 14CF251*

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, James W. and his property; Michael K. and his property; also no contact with Andrew E., Zachory S. and DRM.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
